# Copy to .env — never commit .env
# In File Explorer: if you see ".env.txt", rename to ".env" (Windows hides extensions).
PORT=3333
# No spaces around =. Paste only the secret after = (do not type the word ADMIN_KEY in the login box).
# After editing .env: stop the server (Ctrl+C) and run npm start again.
ADMIN_KEY=set-a-long-random-string-here

# --- Optional: save campaigns from YOUR PC to the LIVE site (no git each time) ---
# After this app is deployed on thetradingcircle.org, set:
# REMOTE_API_URL=https://thetradingcircle.org
# Use the SAME ADMIN_KEY here as on the server’s .env (the live key). Unlock dashboard → Save updates production.
# On the LIVE server’s .env, add (comma-separated, no spaces after commas is fine):
# CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3333,http://127.0.0.1:3333
# If you need to test drafts only on your PC while still saving live, uncomment:
# LOCAL_CAMPAIGN_DATA=1

# ========== PRODUCTION (droplet) — copy to server .env, do NOT commit ==========
# PORT=3334
# ADMIN_KEY=long-random-secret-same-in-admin-ui
# CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3333,http://127.0.0.1:3333
# (Do NOT set REMOTE_API_URL on the server — only on your PC if you save to live from localhost.)
